\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI was referring to the walking vehicles everyone\u2019s been building since the DLC released, but hey, nobody\u2019s built a zombie yet...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-26T06:18:55Z\u0022 title=\u002206/26/2019 06:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by RealKerbal3x\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"neistridlar","CreatedById":20296,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T08:13:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, is there any new code involved here, or is it just using the landing gear code? Either way looks like very useful parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GearsNSuch","CreatedById":190371,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:01:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting part! I can\u0027t wait to see what our engineers will do with this one. I assume it has a PhysicsMaterial with the friction ramped up to max?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, another one for Dinklestein\u0027s! Hooray!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:05:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPutting on my pedant hat, these seem a little pointless.. A whole\u00A0part set for one issue (slippy Walker feet)? Why not simply allow us to adjust the friction levels of any part with a slider?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-26T10:06:29Z\u0022 title=\u002206/26/2019 10:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:21:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561543551\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPutting on my pedant hat, these seem a little pointless.. A whole\u00A0part set for one issue (slippy Walker feet)? Why not simply allow us to adjust the friction levels of any part with a slider?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspect the reason is technical and has to do with the type of collider used for each part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(It\u0027s also not just for one issue, there\u0027s a lot you can do with these.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:24:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561544504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspect the reason is technical and has to do with the type of collider used for each part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(It\u0027s also not just for one issue, there\u0027s a lot you can do with these.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not so sure there is though. Sliding bases would also be better served by being able to adjust friction on the go for any part. Also the part shapes are odd. Why are they so thick? What was the thinking behind each shape?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:34:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625499\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561544674\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not so sure there is though. Sliding bases would also be better served by being able to adjust friction on the go for any part. Also the part shapes are odd. Why are they so thick? What was the thinking behind \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eeach shape?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you don\u0027t want to use them, then don\u0027t use them. They\u0027re certainly just about exactly what I want for certain things -- specifically, very heavy landing legs, and adjustable foundations for bases so that I can get them level. I\u0027m also going to see if I can use them to make wheels by sticking them radially onto a round part\u00A0-- that depends on the type of collider being used, not just the physics material.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe aesthetics are also just about perfect for these jobs. I definitely like them better than being able to adjust friction on any part (which would be just... weird anyway, why would you adjust friction on a solar panel, command pod, or even fuel tank?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:38:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561543551\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPutting on my pedant hat, these seem a little pointless.. A whole\u00A0part set for one issue (slippy Walker feet)? Why not simply allow us to adjust the friction levels of any part with a slider?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the dev reply regarding using them as feet, it seems they\u0027re not specifically for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey seem to be specifically for robotic arms that will grab other craft. Or Kerbals. Or surface features. or... who knows what.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chryssalid 8492","CreatedById":197332,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T10:52:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease include these with the next console update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mindstalker","CreatedById":89250,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T11:37:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625499\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561544674\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not so sure there\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E is though. Sliding bases would also be better served by being able to adjust friction on the go for any part. Also the part shapes are odd. Why are they so thick? What was the thinking behind each shape?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was a thread about this a while ago (I can look it up if you need to). Unity calculated friction in strange ways for non wheeled parts. Its supposed to just average the friction of the surface you are on with the friction of the part, but apparently that gives weird results frequently (no I don\u0027t know why). Specialized parts that have friction specifically programmed into them apparently work better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T11:39:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561546363\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Chryssalid 8492\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Chryssalid 8492 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease include these with the next console update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen the BG DLC releases on console, I assume these will be in it. We just have to wait for Blitworks to port the DLC to console, and for Microsoft/Sony to do their certification process, which is why console releases take so long.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Poodmund","CreatedById":128643,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T12:19:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625499\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561544674\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat was the thinking behind each shape?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple shapes, real easy to model (hardly any geometry changes over a primitive mesh), easy to UV unwrap with mirroring (of which there are some not-so-nice mirroring seams on the diffuse maps of these parts), they suit a primitive collider mesh and can feature really simple diffuse textures which repeating details arrayed across the faces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo like, if you\u0027re a decent 3D artist, you can probably knock all these part models and textures and get them imported into Unity in a small handful hours. I expect the majority of time was spent on getting the friction module sorted and working nicely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maxsimal","CreatedById":160254,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T12:25:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625297\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561510521\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00229293\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jimmidii\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Jimmidii said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the sound of it, these aren\u0027t designed to be grabbers as such, but more non-slip feet for walkers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey were considered for both uses, as you\u0027ll see when you get to read the part descriptions. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T12:50:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625502\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561545534\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the dev reply regarding using them as feet, it seems they\u0027re not specifically for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey seem to be specifically for robotic arms that will grab other craft. Or Kerbals. Or surface features. or... who knows what.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think they work like Docking ports or the claw though. I would just like to hear from the devs their thinking behind each part.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625550\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561551585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128643\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Poodmund\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Poodmund said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple shapes, real easy to model (hardly any geometry changes over a primitive mesh), easy to UV unwrap with mirroring (of which there are some not-so-nice mirroring seams on the diffuse maps of these parts), they suit a primitive collider mesh and can feature really simple diffuse textures which repeating details arrayed across the faces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo like, if you\u0027re a decent 3D artist, you can probably knock all these part models and textures and get them imported into Unity in a small handful hours. I expect the majority of time was spent on getting the friction module sorted and working nicely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure that was part of it yes, it goes without saying that they want to work Efficiently. My question is why the shapes they chose. Did they have a specific purpose in mind.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625501\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561545299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you don\u0027t want to use them, then don\u0027t use them. They\u0027re certainly just about exactly what I want for certain things -- specifically, very heavy landing legs, and adjustable foundations for bases so that I can get them level. I\u0027m also going to see if I can use them to make wheels by sticking them radially onto a round part\u00A0-- that depends on the type of collider being used, not just the physics material.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe aesthetics are also just about perfect for these jobs. I definitely like them better than being able to adjust friction on any part (which would be just... weird anyway, why would you adjust friction on a solar panel, command pod, or even fuel tank?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI never said I didn\u0027t want to use them. I will definitely use them in fact.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I\u0027m just curious as to why squad chose to release all these different shape parts for what is clearly a single Issue, the slippery walkers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T13:47:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625550\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561551585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128643\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Poodmund\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Poodmund said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E like, if you\u0027re a decent 3D artist, you can probably knock all these part models and textures and get them imported into Unity in a small handful hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that\u0027s perfectly fine with me!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI expect that they\u0027ll be great for the \u0022landing legs\u0022 of my big mining rig. (With the caveat that in my current career save the best mining spot on Minmus is on the Greater Flats...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T14:08:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow wasn\u0027t this suggested like a second ago? Nice \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loskene","CreatedById":141778,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T15:04:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625597\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561558103\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow wasn\u0027t this suggested like a second ago? Nice \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt wouldn\u0027t surprise me if most of the \u0022convenience\u0022 additions like these are things the devs have all thought of during the production process, they just wait and see which ones get noticed by the community to justify spending time and resources on them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T16:29:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561553422\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I\u0027m just curious as to why squad chose to release all these different shape parts for what is clearly a single Issue, the slippery walkers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou keep repeating that it\u0027s \u0022clearly a single issue\u0022 when they didn\u0027t even\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Emention\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0that issue in the post announcing them. Why is that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T17:03:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561566555\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou keep repeating that it\u0027s \u0022clearly a single issue\u0022 when they didn\u0027t even\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Emention\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0that issue in the post announcing them. Why is that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause of the many requests for grippier parts so walkers are more feasible. What other reason do you think it\u0027s for?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Slippy\u00A0bases is certainly not the reason to release these parts.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0anyway, that\u0027s my point, the reasons are vague. Using them grab stuff makes zero sense. How and why?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T17:24:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625668\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561568585\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing them grab stuff makes zero sense. How and why?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy attaching them to robotic grabbers and so the grabbed doesn\u0027t slip out of the grasp of the grabbee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T17:30:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561569894\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy attaching them to robotic grabbers and so the grabbed doesn\u0027t slip out of the grasp of the grabbee.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL, what robotic grabbers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-26T17:32:20Z\u0022 title=\u002206/26/2019 05:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T17:35:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561570226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL, what robotic grabbers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRobotic grabbers you might want to design with the new parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, a number of potential uses for the parts have already been proposed to you in this thread. If you\u0027re not interested in them, fine -- but I don\u0027t see the point of pretending that they\u0027re not there and the only possible use is walker feet. (Again, for the record, I\u0027m currently not interested in making walkers, and I very much want them.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-26T17:36:53Z\u0022 title=\u002206/26/2019 05:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Guest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}